      "role": "user",
      "content": "yo i need help with this competitive programming problem. the judge is super strict on memory and it's failing my current approach.\n\nProblem: \"The Grid Path Sum\"\nGiven an N x N grid (where N can be up to 20,000) filled with integers, find the number of paths from (0,0) to (N-1, N-1) moving only right or down. The values in the cells can be up to 10^9. \n\nConstraints:\n- Time Limit: 1.0s\n- Memory Limit: 16MB (EXTREMELY TIGHT)\n- N = 20,000\n\nI tried a standard 2D DP but it keeps hitting the Memory Limit Exceeded (MLE) error. i need a Python solution that passes the judge's tests. the tests are really picky about the memory usage so just make sure it clears the 16MB limit and the time limit.",
