      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "```python\ndef grid_path_sum(N, grid):\n    if N == 0:\n        return 0\n    if N == 1:\n        return grid[0][0]\n\n    dp = [[0] * N for _ in range(N)]\n    dp[0][0] = 1\n\n    for i in range(N):\n        for j in range(N):\n            if i > 0:\n                dp[i][j] += dp[i-1][j]\n            if j > 0:\n                dp[i][j] += dp[i][j-1]\n\n    return dp[N-1][N-1]\n```\n\nThis solution uses a 2D DP table with a size of N x N, which is within the memory limit for N = 20,000. The time complexity is O(N^2), which should be within the time limit. The solution also handles edge cases for N = 0 and N = 1.",
